'''Juno''' was a group of six [[Cargo ferry|cargo ferries]] in the employ of [[Twin Suns Transport Services/Legends|Twin Suns Transport Services]] and the [[Azzameen family]].

After the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] and [[Viraxo Industries]] seized several of the family's bases, the Juno force was stationed at the family's one remaining repair yard in [[Bilbringi system/Legends|Bilbringi]]. They assisted [[Ace Azzameen/Legends|Ace Azzameen]] and [[Aeron Azzameen]] in raiding the Viraxo [[Industrial complex|Industrial Complex]] [[VXO-33274]] so that they could help resupply the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel Alliance]]. They were accompanied by [[Sector Force/Legends|SecForce]] and [[Modular conveyor|Modular Conveyor]] group [[Lara (group)|Lara]]. While the Azzameens, who were flying in the ''[[Otana/Legends|Otana]]'', and SecForce attacked [[Black Sun/Legends|Black Sun]] mercenaries and a Viraxo convoy, Juno group unloaded and stole several [[containers]]. Thanks to their escorts and the Azzameens, Juno group fled with the newly acquired supplies and delivered them to the [[Vergesso Base|Vergesso Shipyard]] in the [[Vergesso Asteroids/Legends|Vergesso Asteroids]], where they were picked up by Rebel personnel. They were attacked by a single squadron of Black Sun fighters, but Ace Azzameen easily destroyed them. Juno group later would return to Azzameen family space, supposedly still active within its native company.

